      "instruction": "<p>Brush a little <strong>cold water </strong>around the edges of the pastry (this helps to seal the pastry!)</p><p>Fold the <strong>pastry</strong> over the filling and seal firmly together, using a fork to crimp along the join</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-18 min or until golden, puffed up and cooked through – this is your <strong>cheesy bean pasty[ies]</strong></p>",
